Tenth Avenue, east side, south from W. 17th Street. Prominently shown is the National Biscuit Company building. This occupies the entire block east to 9th Avenue, from 16th to 15th S8reets. South of same is a one story garae utilizing the 15th to 14th Street
frontage.
View 2 is limited to the National Biscuit Company Building. No. 3 is the same view as No. 1 Photographed after partial demolition for the new elevated roadbed of the New York Central Railroad. This will cross Tenth Avenue to continue on the east side
of same.
Views 1,2: July 16, 1932
View 3: September 6, 1933
P. L. Sperr
